  "prompt": "The resultant of two forces has magnitude 20N. One of the forces has magnitude 20\u221a3N making an angle of 30\u00b0 with the resultant? What is the magnitude of the other force?",
  "response": "To determine the magnitude of the second force, let's analyze the situation using vector components.\n\n1. **Define the Resultant Vector (\\( \\mathbf{R} \\))**:\n   - Magnitude: \\( R = 20 \\) N\n   - Direction: Let's align \\( \\mathbf{R} \\) along the positive x-axis for simplicity.\n\n2. **First Force (\\( \\mathbf{F}_1 \\))**:\n   - Magnitude: \\( F_1 = 20\\sqrt{3} \\) N\n   - Angle with \\( \\mathbf{R} \\): \\( 30^\\circ \\)\n\n3. **Decompose \\( \\mathbf{F}_1 \\) into Components**:\n   - **Along \\( \\mathbf{R} \\) (x-axis)**:\n     \\[\n     F_{1x} = F_1 \\cos(30^\\circ) = 20\\sqrt{3} \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} = 30 \\, \\text{N}\n     \\]\n   - **Perpendicular to \\( \\mathbf{R} \\) (y-axis)**:\n     \\[\n     F_{1y} = F_1 \\sin(30^\\circ) = 20\\sqrt{3} \\times \\frac{1}{2} = 10\\sqrt{3} \\, \\text{N}\n     \\]\n\n4. **Resultant Vector (\\( \\mathbf{R} \\)) Components**:\n   - Since \\( \\mathbf{R} \\) is aligned along the x-axis:\n     \\[\n     R_x = 20 \\, \\text{N}, \\quad R_y = 0 \\, \\text{N}\n     \\]\n\n5. **Determine the Second Force (\\( \\mathbf{F}_2 \\))**:\n   - \\( \\mathbf{F}_2 = \\mathbf{R} - \\mathbf{F}_1 \\)\n   - **x-component**:\n     \\[\n     F_{2x} = R_x - F_{1x} = 20 - 30 = -10 \\, \\text{N}\n     \\]\n   - **y-component**:\n     \\[\n     F_{2y} = R_y - F_{1y} = 0 - 10\\sqrt{3} = -10\\sqrt{3} \\, \\text{N}\n     \\]\n\n6. **Calculate the Magnitude of \\( \\mathbf{F}_2 \\)**:\n   \\[\n   |\\mathbf{F}_2| = \\sqrt{F_{2x}^2 + F_{2y}^2} = \\sqrt{(-10)^2 + (-10\\sqrt{3})^2} = \\sqrt{100 + 300} = \\sqrt{400} = 20 \\, \\text{N}\n   \\]\n\n**Final Answer:**  \nThe magnitude of the other force is\u202f20\u202fN.",
